@purplewarp  I watched first 5 episodes. Dante got kidnapped twice. First by Lady, second because of Lady. She killed more demons than Dante. When her squad got wiped out, she basically soloed the entire building. Figured out Rabbit's plan and had all around more screen time than Dante who is supposed to be the main character. At the end of the episode 5, she ordered a rescue mission, which she had no authorization to approve that got all the refugees killed.

She did more good when alone than with others. She has no regard for the chain of command within her own organization. She has more screen time than the main character. Most of the problems in the show are caused by her and could be avoided if she actually thought things through.

Textbook definition of a girlboss

@xervislane770 
Like, it’s okay if you didn’t like it and all, but it’s not a bad story. 
I understand that Dante is weaker, doesn’t have Ebony and Ivory, and doesn’t know his full abilities yet. Just wait for the anime to progress. It’s not canon, but it seems to be following a path similar to the beginning of Devil May Cry. In the manga, the rabbit even appears (he wasn’t human, he was just a demon possessing a doll), and he tells Dante that Vergil is alive.

